segment.source: While the Internet Explorer Customization Wizard has been around for quite a while, there are still some known issues that you might encounter while deploying or managing your custom IE install package.
segment.target: While the Internet Explorer Customization Wizard has been around for quite a while, there are still some known issues that you might encounter while deploying or managing your custom IE install package.

segment.source: I can’t locate some of the wizard pages
segment.target: I can’t locate some of the wizard pages

segment.source: The most common reasons you won’t see certain pages is because:
segment.target: The most common reasons you won’t see certain pages is because:

segment.source: Your licensing agreement with Microsoft.
segment.target: Your licensing agreement with Microsoft.

segment.source: Your licensing agreement determines whether you install the Internal or External version of the Internet Explorer Customization Wizard, and there are different features available for each version.
segment.target: Your licensing agreement determines whether you install the Internal or External version of the Internet Explorer Customization Wizard, and there are different features available for each version.

segment.source: For info about which features are available for each version, see Determine the licensing version and features to use in IEAK 11.
segment.target: For info about which features are available for each version, see Determine the licensing version and features to use in IEAK 11.

segment.source: Your choice of operating system.
segment.target: Your choice of operating system.

segment.source: Depending on the operating system you picked from the Platform Selection page of the wizard, you might not see all of the pages.
segment.target: Depending on the operating system you picked from the Platform Selection page of the wizard, you might not see all of the pages.

segment.source: Some features aren’t available for all operating systems.
segment.target: Some features aren’t available for all operating systems.

segment.source: For more information, see Use the Platform Selection page in the IEAK 11 Wizard.
segment.target: For more information, see Use the Platform Selection page in the IEAK 11 Wizard.

segment.source: Your choice of features.
segment.target: Your choice of features.

segment.source: Depending on what you selected from the Feature Selection page of the wizard, you might not see all of the pages.
segment.target: Depending on what you selected from the Feature Selection page of the wizard, you might not see all of the pages.

segment.source: You need to make sure that the features you want to customize are all checked.
segment.target: You need to make sure that the features you want to customize are all checked.

segment.source: For more information, see Use the Feature Selection page in the IEAK 11 Wizard.
segment.target: For more information, see Use the Feature Selection page in the IEAK 11 Wizard.

segment.target: Internet Explorer Setup fails on employee devices

segment.source: Various issues can cause problems during Setup, including missing files, trust issues, or URL monikers.
segment.target: Various issues can cause problems during Setup, including missing files, trust issues, or URL monikers.

segment.source: You can troubleshoot these issues by reviewing the Setup log file, located at from the Windows folder (typically, ).

segment.source: The log file covers the entire Setup process from the moment IE11Setup.exe starts until the last .cab file finishes, providing error codes that you can use to help determine the cause of the failure.

segment.source: Internet Explorer Setup connection times out
segment.target: Internet Explorer Setup connection times out

segment.source: Internet Explorer Setup can switch servers during the installation process to maintain maximum throughput or to recover from a non-responsive download site (you receive less than 1 byte in 2 minutes).
segment.target: Internet Explorer Setup can switch servers during the installation process to maintain maximum throughput or to recover from a non-responsive download site (you receive less than 1 byte in 2 minutes).

segment.source: If the connection times out, but Setup is able to connect to the next download site on the list, your download starts over.
segment.target: If the connection times out, but Setup is able to connect to the next download site on the list, your download starts over.

segment.source: If however the connection times out and Setup can’t connect to a different server, it’ll ask if you want to stop the installation or try again.
segment.target: If however the connection times out and Setup can’t connect to a different server, it’ll ask if you want to stop the installation or try again.
